  <brief_title>Influence of Polymorphisms in the ATP6V1 Gene of the V-ATPase on the Development of Incomplete Distal Renal Tubular Acidosis</brief_title>
  <official_title>Comparison of Furosemide/Fludrocortisone With Ammonium Chloride Loading Test in the Diagnosis of Incomplete dRTA in Kidney Stone Formers</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>University Hospital Inselspital, Berne</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University Hospital Inselspital, Berne</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Purpose

        1. To compare the performance of the two currently employed urinary acidifications tests in
           stone formers, the furosemide/fludrocortisone and ammonium chloride loading test.

        2. To study the impact of polymorphisms in the genes ATP6V1B1, ATP6V0A4 and SLC4A1 on
           urinary acidification in stone formers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
